ğŸ”¹ Hashing kya hota hai?
Hashing ek process hai jisme plain text data ko ek fixed-length ke unreadable value (hash) me convert kiya jata hai.
Important point: 
            - Hashing one-way process hota hai. 
            - Hash se original data wapas nahi nikala ja sakta.

ğŸ”¹ Hashing ki need kyun hoti hai?
Socho tumne database me aise data rakha:
                                      Username: meraz
                                      Password: 123456
  âŒ Problem:
           - Agar hacker DB hack kar le â†’ password directly mil jayega
           - Sab users risk me aa jayenge.



ğŸ”¹ Plain Text âŒ â†’ Encryption âŒ â†’ Hashing âœ… (Flow) :

1ï¸âƒ£ Plain Text Storage (âŒ Worst) :
                                 - password = "123456"
                                          - Easy to read.
                                          - Hacker ko direct mil jata hai.
2ï¸âƒ£ Encryption (âš ï¸ Better but not best) :
                                  - Encrypted password = "A@x9#Lp"
                                                   - Data hide hota hai.
                                                   - Lekin decryption key hoti hai.
                                                   - Agar key leak ho gayi â†’ password wapas mil jayega.
3ï¸âƒ£ Hashing (âœ… Best for passwords) :
                                - password = "123456"
                                  hash = "$2a$10$hjs7Kjs9..."
                                         - Hash se original password kabhi wapas nahi milta.
                                         - Even developer bhi nahi dekh sakta password.
                                         - Hacker ke liye useless.

ğŸ”¹ Real Life Example :
ğŸ§ ATM PIN Example : ATM machine kya karta hai?
1ï¸âƒ£ Tum PIN enter karte ho :
                           - PIN = 1234
2ï¸âƒ£ ATM uska hash banata hai:
                       - hash(1234) = X9@kLp
3ï¸âƒ£ Database me already stored hota hai:
                           - X9@kLp
4ï¸âƒ£ Compare hota hai:
                  - Entered PIN ka hash == Stored hash ?
âœ”ï¸ Match â†’ Access
âŒ No match â†’ Reject.



Note:- Java me hash table ek concept hai, koi separate class nahi. HashMap aur Hashtable dono is concept ke alag implementations hain, aur dono Map interface ko implement karte hain.

ğŸ“¦ Hash Table (Concept) :
--------------------------
ğŸ”¹ Definition :
Hash table ek data structure concept hai jo hashing technique ka use karke data ko keyâ€“value pairs ke form me store karta hai aur fast insertion, search aur deletion provide karta hai.

ğŸ”¹ Key Idea :
Key se hash â†’ hash se index â†’ index par keyâ€“value store.




ğŸ”¹ Hash Function Design Techniques (for Hash Tables) :
------------------------------------------------------

1ï¸âƒ£ Division Method :
ğŸ”¹ Formula : h(k) = k % m                                                            search keys ->   {11,10,66,58,74} 
                          k â†’ key                                                                           .............
                          m â†’ table size                                                                  0 |           |
                                                                                                            |           |
                                                                                                            '''''''''''''
                                                                                                          1 |           |
2ï¸âƒ£ Mid-Square Method :                                                                                      |           |   
ğŸ”¹ Steps :                                                                                                   ''''''''''''
      - Key ka square karo.                                                                                  
      - Beech ke digits uthao.
      - ğŸ”¹ Example : (2-digit index chahiye)
                             Key = 11
                             Square = 121
                             Pad with 0 â†’ 0121
                             Middle 2 digits â†’ 12
               Zero padding allowed hai âœ”ï¸


3ï¸âƒ£ Digit Folding Method :
ğŸ”¹ Idea :
      - Key ke digits ko parts me tod ke add karo.
      - ğŸ”¹ Example :
                    Key = 123456
                    Fold â†’ 12 + 34 + 56 = 102
                    Index = 102 % tableSize
ğŸ”¹ Use :
      - Jab key bahut badi ho (mobile number).















